<item>
            <title>[HBASE-4076] hbase should pick up HADOOP_CONF_DIR on its classpath</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4076</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, hbase doesn&apos;t automatically include the hadoop config on its classpath. It usually works out OK since we specify hbase.rootdir with a fullly qualified hdfs://nnhost/path URL. But, in secure environments for example, there are some other Hadoop configs that need to be available to HBase (eg NN krb5 principal info).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should change the HBase scripts to automatically pick up HADOOP_CONF_DIR or HADOOP_HOME/conf on the classpath when available.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
